controlled by the \u003Cstrong\u003EC5 and C6\u003C/strong\u003E myotomes. These myotomes innervate the biceps brachii and brachialis muscles, which are the main muscles responsible for flexing the elbow.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC3, C4\u003C/strong\u003E are not involved in elbow flexion. These myotomes are associated with neck movements and shoulder elevation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC4, C5\u003C/strong\u003E are involved in shoulder abduction and some shoulder movements.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC6, C7\u003C/strong\u003E are involved in wrist extension and some finger movements, but C6 is part of the elbow flexion myotome, but not C7.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EC7, C8\u003C/strong\u003E are primarily responsible for elbow extension and finger flexion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Elbow flexion is primarily controlled by the C5 and C6 myotomes.","Understanding myotomes is crucial for assessing neurological function and localising lesions in the spinal cord or peripheral nerves."],"references":["Sonoo M. Recent advances in neuroanatomy: the myotome update. J Neurol Neurosurg Psychiatry. 2023 Aug;94(8):643-648. doi: 10.1136/jnnp-2022-329696. Epub 2023 Jan 18. PMID: 36653172.","Kaiser JT, Lugo-Pico JG. Neuroanatomy, Spinal Nerves. [Updated 2023 Aug 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK542218/","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Michael-Titus, A. T., \u0026 Shortland, P. (2022). The Nervous System, E-Book: The Nervous System, E-Book. Elsevier Health Science","Howard, R., Kullmann, D., Werring, D., \u0026 Zandi, M. (Eds.). (2024). Neurology: a queen square textbook. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"63213"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"q